{
  "stem": "1873.1",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 12.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But this was a strange situation, because they grabbed everybody, even people who were obvious not able to work-- old men.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So it was, from the beginning, suspicious.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "On top of it, there was no news.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So then we asked-- I remember my father had a friend, a Pole, and the other people-- asked Christian friends that if something will happen again, some kind of round-up similar to it, they should go after the train and find out where the train is going, especially when we heard in other towns nearby the same thing happened.",
      "word_count": 59
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "It didn't take long-- beginning of May.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Izbica was again surrounded.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They grabbed about 1,500 people, loaded in the train.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "The train was waiting [INAUDIBLE] in the station.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And the train moved eastward.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But this time, the Poles which were alert went after the train.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And it didn't take long.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "The same day, they returned and told us a strange story-- unbelievable story-- that about 40 miles farther is a place called Belzec.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And they're killing people there, simple like that.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So we realized that [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] the Germans are killing Jews.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But, you see, they have done it in a very special way.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It was-- they planned it, probably, this way.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Because in the beginning, they asked the Judenrat-- now, Judenrat was an organization of the elders-- elder, elder-- the elders of the Jews, which in a way cooperated with the Nazis.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It wasn't a voluntary organization.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "The Nazis established, these are called Judenrat.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "There were about a dozen very well known Jews.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And the orders were first given to the Judenrat, and the Judenrat implemented.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "In the beginning, the Judenrat was ordered to deliver 1,000, 2,000 people.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And the Judenrat picked up, of course, some cripples, old people.",
      "word_count": 11
    }
  ],
